# ── WORKFLOW 2: MORNING SUMMARY ──────────────────────────

## Node order (complete)
```
Cron → Get Overnight KEYS → Code: Split Keys → Redis GET each key → Code: Build Conversation → Message a model3 → Code in JavaScript4 → HTTP Request3
```
> Delete the old **Code in JavaScript3** — replace with the 3 nodes below.

---

## REPLACE Code in JavaScript3 with these 3 nodes:

### Node 1 – Code: Split Keys
(Connects from Get Overnight Data1)

```javascript
// Compute yesterday in IST
const now = new Date();
const istDate = new Date(
  now.toLocaleString('en-US', { timeZone: 'Asia/Kolkata' })
);
istDate.setDate(istDate.getDate() - 1);

const yesterday = [
  istDate.getFullYear(),
  String(istDate.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, '0'),
  String(istDate.getDate()).padStart(2, '0'),
].join('-');

// Redis KEYS returns array in $json.value
const allKeys = $json.value || [];

// Keep only yesterday's afterhours keys, skip empty-phone keys
const keys = allKeys.filter(k =>
  k.includes(`:${yesterday}`) && !k.includes('afterhours::')
);

if (keys.length === 0) return [];

// One item per key → each goes through Redis GET separately
return keys.map(key => ({
  json: { redisKey: key, date: yesterday }
}));
```

---

### Node 2 – Redis GET each key (NEW node, after Split Keys)

| Setting | Value |
|---|---|
| Operation | [get](file:///c:/Users/DhruvVaghasiya/Desktop/Backup/Looks%20Workflow/Looks%20automation/src/data/mockData.js#117-146) |
| Key | `={{ $json.redisKey }}` |

> This works because the after-hours workflow now stores data as a JSON string (not a list).

---

### Node 3 – Code: Build Conversation (NEW node, after Redis GET)

```javascript
const redisKey = $('Split Keys').item.json.redisKey;
const date = $('Split Keys').item.json.date;

// Extract phone from key: afterhours:PHONE:DATE
const parts = redisKey.split(':');
const phone = parts[1] || 'Unknown';

// Parse the JSON array stored by the after-hours workflow
let history = [];
try {
  const raw = $json.value;
  if (raw) history = JSON.parse(raw);
  if (!Array.isArray(history)) history = [];
} catch {
  history = [];
}

if (history.length === 0) return [];

// Format for the AI summarizer
const conversation = history
  .map(m => `Time: ${m.time}\nCustomer: ${m.customer}\nBot: ${m.bot}`)
  .join('\n\n');

return [{
  json: {
    phone,
    date,
    conversation,
    messageCount: history.length,
  }
}];
```

